      "A lot of what is thought is complicated, there are some teachers like de docent (not only him) who speaks in circles. for example he says one thing one and then says the opposite within the same breath (make sure to drink water its important juice isnt good for u but its ok to drink lots of juice and no water)  that circle way of speaking leaves students confused, even after asking him questions he still will give you different answers each time to the same question. this riddle like teaching because they dont want to give too much guidance away is annoying and difficult to deal with. Especially in the international course where students are already learning in a language that they are not native too its already difficult to understand 1000% as is and add the riddles to it then everyone gets confused on what to do and things become extremely unclear. not only that but there is so much time spent in speaking in the circles that the main things we should take away from the lesson completely flies over our heads alot of the time.",
