      "Teachers should improve their communication skills. There were multiple situations in which one teacher said one thing and the other said something else; for example, one teacher announced that there is no Colloquium on Wednesday, even though 10 minutes earlier another teacher had invited everyone to the same Colloquium. This situation would be avoided if teachers communicated more effectively with one another.  Another problem was the teacher's communication with students. For example, one student's grade was swapped with another student's grade (which I personally think is unacceptable at this level). The way it was communicated to them was totally unacceptable. They were only given the information that 'There was an error,' which is completely the wrong way to communicate such a message. There should be a formal meeting with students and the teacher, with formal apologies and an explanation of the results.",
